The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, June 30, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, June 29: Amit Kiran Deb has been appointed state chief secretary in a bureaucratic shuffle. He will take over on Thursday. 

 Deb, now in charge of the home department, succeeds Asok Gupta, who is set to retire. Power secretary Prasad Ranjan Roy will take Debs place. Roy will be succeeded by public enterprises and industrial reconstruction secretary Sunil Mitra.

 Calcutta: Manotosh Roy, former Mr Universe, died at a city nursing home on Wednesday night following a cardiac arrest. He was 88. Roy had won the title in 1951.

 Calcutta: Industry minister Nirupam Sen has told the Assembly that the Metal Box Company has not shown interest in reopening its unit despite the governments offer of a soft loan.The minister said the government had also invited Metal Box authorities to hold talks, but they never turned up.

 Calcutta: The CPM on Wednesday accepted economist Arjun Sengupta as the sixth candidate for the forthcoming Rajya Sabha elections, slated for July 14.

 Krishnagar: A 24-year-old woman has committed suicide to escape the torture inflicted by her alcoholic husband. 




